  "response": "Mint.com was co-founded by Aaron Patzer, who also played a significant role in its design and development. Launched in 2007, Mint.com aimed to help users manage their finances by providing tools for budgeting, tracking expenses, and monitoring financial accounts in one place. The website's user-friendly interface and intuitive design contributed to its popularity, making it one of the leading personal finance management tools before its acquisition by Intuit in 2009.",
